{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "In sum, the high scores of Llama 2 and GPT-4 across all dimensions confirm the general capability of LLMs to generate explanations that users perceive as detailed and comprehensible.",
    "Second, GPT-3.5 recorded the lowest explainability scores across all three evaluated dimensions when compared to its counterparts.",
    "The difference in scores between GPT-3.5 and the other LLMs are statistically significant across all questions, especially between Llama 2 and GPT-3.5 (p < 0.001).",
    "The most substantial difference is the perceived level of detail between Llama 2 and GPT-3.5 (\"The explanation of the LLM is sufficiently detailed\") with a mean score of 4.2 (SE = 0.074) for Llama 2 in contrast to a mean score of 3.2 (SE = 0.1) for GPT-3.5 (see Web Appendix Table A6).",
    "Third, trustworthiness is the dimension that received the lowest average scores from respondents for all LLMs (GPT-3.5 = 3.2 (SE = 0.073); GPT-4 = 3.4 (SE = 0.074); Llama 2 = 3.6 (SE = 0.072))."
